<section id="section--the-process">
	<h2>The Process</h2>
	
	<ol>
		<li>
			Receive some input. This can be any positive integer.
		</li>
		<li>
			<ol>
				<li>If the input is odd multiply it by 3 then add 1.</li>
				<li>If the input is even divide it by 2.</li>
			</ol>
		</li>
		<li>
			Repeat.
		</li>
	</ol>
	
	<figure>
		<figcaption>example 1</figcaption>
	
		<div id="calculation-steps--example-1">
			<div>
				<p><strong>Input:</strong> <span class="numbers">10</span></p>
				<div class="arithmatic">10 &divide; 2 &equals; 5</div>
				<div class="arithmatic">(5 &times; 3) &plus; 1 &equals; 16</div>
				<div class="arithmatic">16 &divide; 2 &equals; 8</div>
				<div class="arithmatic">8 &divide; 2 &equals; 4</div>
				<div class="arithmatic">4 &divide; 2 &equals; 2</div>
				<div class="arithmatic">2 &divide; 2 &equals; <span class="solution">1</span></div>
				<div class="arithmatic">(1 &times; 3) &plus; 1 &equals; 4</div>
				<div class="arithmatic">4 &divide; 2 &equals; 2</div>
				<div class="arithmatic">2 &divide; 2 &equals; <span class="solution">1</span></div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</figure>
	
	<p>As you can see, once the result hits 4, 2, or 1 the steps will always be the same and repeat forever.</p>
</section><!-- /#section--the-process -->